By placing the diagnostic and rehabilitation centers at the village level, you transform a potentially frightening concept (a "robot prison") into a "Community Technology Health Center."

Localized Ownership: If a robot in a specific village starts behaving erratically, it is quarantined in the local village colony. The citizens of that village don't have to wait for a state official to come; the local Trustee and the Citizen-Auditors can examine the log immediately.

The Learning Loop: By making the logs of the "rehabilitated" robots publicly viewable, you create a Knowledge Exchange. If a robot in one village fails due to a specific soil condition or a common local task, the "fix" (the software patch or hardware adjustment) is instantly available to every other village.

Community Science: You are effectively turning the entire nation into a giant, decentralized research lab. Every error is a lesson; every fix is a contribution to the national "Bumblebee" stack.
